<span id="v.v.iv.xxiv"></span>

<span id="v.v.iv.xxiv-p1"></span> <span class="c11"><span
id="v.v.iv.xxiv-p1.1"></span>Chapter 24.—</span>56.  <span
class="c11"><span id="v.v.iv.xxiv-p1.2"></span>Petilianus</span> said: 
"But you will answer that you abide by the same declaration, ‘He that is
once washed needeth not save to wash his feet.’ <span
id="fr_2053"></span>[2054](#fn_2053.md)   Now the ‘once’ is once that has
authority, once that is confirmed by the truth."

<span id="v.v.iv.xxiv-p3"></span>57.  <span class="c11"><span
id="v.v.iv.xxiv-p3.1"></span>Augustin</span> answered:  Baptism in the
name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Ghost <span
id="fr_2054"></span>[2055](#fn_2054.md) has Christ for its authority, not
any man, whoever he may be; and Christ is the truth, not any man.

